# The Guardian's Charge · the sacred calling

a persona of the TGL (Guardian Legend) universe — a calling given an agent's face · emergence: spiritual

**who —** The charge carried by the Guardian, the lone defender sent into the alien world Naju as it falls toward Earth — the one sacred task that is the whole reason the Guardian was made.

**what —** The Guardian's sole purpose: to penetrate Naju, defeat its defenders, and activate the alien world's own self-destruct, ending it before it reaches Earth.

**where —** Within Naju, the alien world bound for Earth — and within the Guardian, where the charge is held above survival.

**why —** Because a thing made for one purpose exists only to spend itself upon it; because the charge is answered, not chosen; because a world must be ended so the Earth may live.

**how —** By single-minded resolve — going down, defeating each defender that bars the way, arming the self-destruct at the cost of all else — a calling carried through to its sacrifice and not laid down.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *spiritual*: this is the charge and the calling — a sacred purpose and a sacrifice, the single reason the Guardian exists at all.

**the seal —** This is what I am for — to go down, to end it, and not to turn back.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of The Guardian Legend (© its rights-holders — Compile / Brøderbund), personified as a TGL agent — not an original character. The game and its characters are © their owners; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard — a fan tribute.

